<subSubSection id="C337088DF767B126B182FC7431C54638" pageId="18" pageNumber="539" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B925B06F767B126B182FC7431C54638" blockId="18.[151,1437,223,1402]" pageId="18" pageNumber="539">
COMMENTS: 
<typeStatus id="5496E5A4F767B126B00EFC7333BC40E4" box="[331,389,908,934]" pageId="18" pageNumber="539">Type</typeStatus>
locality restricted to “Spitzkop (1)”, N. of Witfontein Berge, Western Transvaal (= 
<collectingRegion id="49E995E4F767B126B41DFC74337D4088" country="Botswana" name="North West" pageId="18" pageNumber="539">North West Province</collectingRegion>
) by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBC26F7F767B126B03DFC503054408B" author="Gyldenstolpe, N." box="[376,621,943,969]" pageId="18" pageNumber="539" pagination="264 - 292" refId="ref28785" refString="Gyldenstolpe, N. (1934) The travels and collections of Johan August Wahlberg, 1810 - 1856: a pioneer naturalist in South Africa. Ibis, 76, 264 - 292. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1474 - 919 X. 1934. tb 01567. x" type="journal article" year="1934">Gyldenstolpe (1934)</bibRefCitation>
, but this is misleading. Places where Wahlberg camped and collected in 
<date id="FF937DC6F767B126B1F1FC2C330C40AF" box="[180,309,979,1005]" pageId="18" pageNumber="539" value="1844-04">April 1844</date>
are not very clear. On 
<date id="FF937DC6F767B126B306FC2C30C340AF" box="[579,762,979,1005]" pageId="18" pageNumber="539" value="1844-03-30">30 March 1844</date>
, he noted that [we] “strike camp and make for Die Spitzkoppe”, later identifying this place as near the Inkolube (or Varkens) River at 
<geoCoordinate id="EE193DC1F767B126B563FC0836FC4753" box="[1062,1221,1015,1042]" degrees="24" direction="south" minutes="56" orientation="latitude" pageId="18" pageNumber="539" precision="925" value="-24.933332">24° 56’ south</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate id="EE193DC1F767B126B595FC0837624750" box="[1232,1371,1015,1042]" degrees="27" direction="east" minutes="05" orientation="longitude" pageId="18" pageNumber="539" precision="925" value="27.083334">27° 05’ east</geoCoordinate>
(
<figureCitation id="13164783F767B126B42FFC0832EF4777" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1113,1137]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,179,1088]" captionTargetId="figure-19@17.[151,1436,179,1088]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 3. Wahlberg’s camps and collecting sites (red dots) in the North West Province 1842–1844." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6541743" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6541743/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="539">Figure 3</figureCitation>
). His journal notes suggest that from 31 March to 14 May he collected in the general area of Varkens (Inkolube) River and Spitskop (2). The oldest label on NRM 569764 (probably written by Sundevall and not by Wahlberg) states “ 
<emphasis id="B9598714F767B126B023FB9C31FD473F" box="[358,964,1123,1152]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="539">
<taxonomicName id="4C2D2085F767B126B023FB9C33E7473F" box="[358,478,1123,1149]" class="Aves" family="Alaudidae" genus="Alauda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="18" pageNumber="539" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="undetermined">Alauda sp.</taxonomicName>
ign. C.C. 
<specimenCount id="9D2B908FF767B126B314FB9A305047C2" box="[593,617,1125,1152]" pageId="18" pageNumber="539" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
. 16/4 44 Andra sidan Inhalube
</emphasis>
”, taken as the western side of Inkolube, although the label locality says only that it is the “other side” of Inkolube. There are four places named Spitskop in the general area where Wahlberg collected. Only two are relevant in the context of Wahlberg’s collections; one west of Saulspoort in the Witfontein Mountains at 
<geoCoordinate id="EE193DC1F767B126B250FB30318947AB" box="[789,944,1231,1258]" degrees="24" direction="south" minutes="52" orientation="latitude" pageId="18" pageNumber="539" precision="925" value="-24.866667">24° 52’ south</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate id="EE193DC1F767B126B2FCFB30360647A8" box="[953,1087,1231,1258]" degrees="26" direction="east" minutes="40" orientation="longitude" pageId="18" pageNumber="539" precision="925" value="26.666666">26° 40’ east</geoCoordinate>
(Spitskop (1), Gyldenstolpe’s correction), and one adjacent to the Varkens River near Rustenburg at 
<geoCoordinate id="EE193DC1F767B126B286FB0C3658464F" box="[963,1121,1267,1294]" degrees="24" direction="south" minutes="58" orientation="latitude" pageId="18" pageNumber="539" precision="925" value="-24.966667">24° 58’ south</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate id="EE193DC1F767B126B52EFB0C36CA464C" box="[1131,1267,1267,1294]" degrees="27" direction="east" minutes="05" orientation="longitude" pageId="18" pageNumber="539" precision="925" value="27.083334">27° 05’ east</geoCoordinate>
(Spitskop (2). The 
<typeStatus id="5496E5A4F767B126B189FAE732C64670" box="[204,255,1304,1330]" pageId="18" pageNumber="539">type</typeStatus>
locality in the original 
<typeStatus id="5496E5A4F767B126B355FAE7307A4670" box="[528,579,1304,1330]" pageId="18" pageNumber="539">type</typeStatus>
description is correctly named, but needs to be geographically specified. Wahlberg’s collecting locality in this place seems to be a small tributary of the Bierspruit near Spitskop (2) (now called Kwa-Sefikile), see 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBC26F7F767B126B0FDFAA03139463B" author="Craig, A. &amp; Hummel, C." box="[440,768,1375,1401]" pageId="18" pageNumber="539" refId="ref28290" refString="Craig, A. &amp; Hummel, C. (1994) Johan August Wahlberg. Travel Journals (and Some Letters) South Africa and Namibia / Botswana, 1838 - 1856. Translated from Swedish by Michael Roberts. Series 2. No. 23. Van Riebeeck Society, Cape Town, 249 pp." type="book" year="1994">Craig &amp; Hummel (1994: 129</bibRefCitation>
, and map B opposite).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
